[SN]TITLE[SN]
Two people arrested over spate of thefts in West Dunbartonshire

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Two people have been arrested over a spate of thefts in West Dunbartonshire.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 29-year-old man and 33-year-old woman were detained following a police operation in Clydebank on Thursday.
Officers were investigating thefts in the town and nearby Old Kilpatrick between 6 May and 29 June.
The man was arrested in connection with nine thefts and will be reported to prosecutors over a further 31 others. The woman was arrested in connection with eight thefts.
